  <thing id="io5CShrdXln" name="Shard of Xeluan" description="{b}Empowered Magic.{/b} While holding this gold and silver-veined obsidian shard, you can use it as a spellcasting focus, and it grants you a +1 bonus to your spell attack rolls.\n\n{b}Enhanced Strength.{/b} Your Strength score increases by 4 while the shard is on your person, up to a maximum of 22.\n\n{b}Curse.{/b} Attuning to this cursed item extends that curse to you. You remain cursed until you are targeted by the {i}remove curse{/i} spell or similar magic, or until the shard is reattached to Xeluan&apos;s petrified heart.\nWhen you roll a 1 on an attack roll, an ability check, or a saving throw, roll 1d6 and consult the list below to determine the misfortune that befalls you due to the curse. For as long as this misfortune lasts, no other shard misfortunes befall you.\n\n{b}1.{/b} You accidentally cut yourself on the shard and are poisoned until the next dawn.\n{b}2.{/b} A vision of ancient city threatened by crumbling mountains and erupting volcanoes causes you to be stunned until the end of your next turn.\n{b}3.{/b} The ground beneath you briefly shakes. You and each creature within 10 feet of you must succeed on a DC 16 Dexterity save or be knocked prone.\n{b}4.{/b} The shard releases three glowing darts of magical force that target one random creature within 30 feet of you. If no such target exists, they instead target you. Each dart hits automatically and deals 3 (1d4 + 1) force damage to its target.\n{b}5.{/b} Until the next dawn, Beasts with an Intelligence score of 3 or lower treat you with hostility.\n{b}6.{/b} Until the next dawn, you make all ability checks with disadvantage." compset="Wondrous">
    <usesource source="5eKftGVA"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="EquipAvail"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="NeedAttune"/>
    <tag group="Custom" tag="5CEbArcFoc"/>
    <tag group="ItemRarity" tag="Rare"/>
    <tag group="GearType" tag="gtWondrous"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="EquipMag"/>
    <eval phase="PreLevel" priority="5000">doneif (field[gIsAttuned].value = 0)

      ~modify strength
      hero.child[aSTR].field[Bonus].value += 4
      hero.child[aSTR].field[aMaxValue].value = maximum(hero.child[aSTR].field[aMaxValue].value,22)
      
      doneif (field[gIsEquip].value = 0)

      foreach pick in hero from Spellcast
        eachpick.field[cSplAttack].value += 1
        nexteach</eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="io5CCnstPrtrt" name="Constantori&apos;s Portrait" description="This painting depicts a beautiful courtier. it is a Small object with AC 12, 20 hit points, and immunity to poison damage. WIth its gold-leaf frame, the painting weighs 15 pounds. If the painting has at least 1 hit point and is targeted by the {i}mending{/i} spell, it regains 2d6 hit points.\n\n{b}Sentience.{/b}The portrait is a sentient, lawful evil item with an Intelligence 14, Wisdom 12, and Charisma 8. It can hear within a range of 120 feet and has darkvision within a range of 60 feet, but it can only see things in front of itself.\nThe painting speaks Common, Draconic, and Elvish as if it were a living person, though its mouth doesn&apos;t move. Whenever conversation occurs within the portrait&apos;s auditory range, the painting happily gathers secrets, the names of secret tellers, significant events, or any political conversations.\n\n{b}Personality.{/b} The portrait is demanding, demeaning, and full of itself. It hates being covered or being placed out of sight, and it has extremely harsh words for anyone that tries to remove its ornate frame.\n\n{b}Wealth of Information.{/b} The painting&apos;s was created to observe and recall conversations. Over the past few decades, it has quietly witnessed countless conversations and now knows an incredible amount of lore, from criminal conspiracies to secret passwords. The DM ultimately determines what knowledge the painting possesses.\nWhile attuned to the painting, you can use an action to telepathically contact it from any distance, so long as you and the painting are on the same plane of existence. The painting can&apos;t telepathically contact you, however. Maintaining telepathic contact with the painting requires your concentration (as if concentrating on a spell).\n\n{b}Guardian Portrait.{/b} While you are attuned to the painting, you can command it to guard its location against one or more creatures you identify as enemies. The painting performs this function until you command it to stop or until your attunement to the painting ends.\nThe painting has 3 charges. When a creature, identified by the painting as its enemy, begins its turn in a space the painting can see, the painting spends 1 of its charges to cast {i}magic missile{/i} (3 missiles), targeting that creature. The painting regains all spent charges each dawn." compset="Wondrous">
    <fieldval field="gWeight" value="15"/>
    <fieldval field="trkMax" value="20"/>
    <usesource source="5eKftGVA"/>
